'''"Dewback"''' was the [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Rebel SpecForce]] [[Callsign/Legends|call sign]] for a Rebel SpecForce sentinel, in the [[Corellian Sector (Nar Shaddaa)/Legends|Corellian Sector]] of [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]]. "Dewback" was the sentinel who told "[[Stardog One]]" that two light freighters approaching the sector were actually disguised [[Gamma-class assault shuttle/Legends|''Gamma''-class assault shuttles]].

==Behind the scenes==
In the printed version of ''[[A Hunter's Fate: Greedo's Tale]]'', [[Spane Covis]]'s Rebel SpecForce call sign was [[Dewback (call sign)|''Dewback'']]. However, in the [[Star Wars comic books|webstrip]] version, Spane Covis's dialogue is divided between two characters: a [[Human/Legends|Human]] whose name is not directly stated, and a [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] who uses the callsign "Dewback".

